A sleeping princess in an elaborate Victorian-era ballgown lying peacefully on a bed of glowing green circuit boards and server racks, her dress transitioning from deep blue velvet into flowing streams of golden binary code and data particles. The scene is set in a grand castle server room where gothic stone arches frame rows of humming machines with blinking lights. Warm amber light streams through stained glass windows depicting coffee cups (the Java symbol). Delicate vines of ethernet cables wind around ornate pillars. The princess's hair cascades down, interweaving with fiber optic strands that pulse with increasing brightness, suggesting an awakening. Vintage sepia-toned photograph aesthetic with hand-tinted color accents, aged paper texture, and soft vignette edges reminiscent of 1890s fairy tale book illustrations.
